# Privacy Policy — Frenzy Stack

**Last Updated: March 2026**
**Effective Date: March 2026**

This Privacy Policy describes how **Frenzy Stack** ("App", "we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, and shares information when you use our mobile game available on the Apple App Store and Google Play Store.

By downloading or using Frenzy Stack, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.

---

## 1. Information We Collect

### 1.1 Information You Provide
- **Player Name / Nickname**: An optional display name you choose for the global leaderboard. This name is publicly visible to other players.

### 1.2 Information Collected Automatically
- **Anonymous Player ID**: A randomly generated UUID (Universally Unique Identifier) created on your device. This ID is not linked to your identity.
- **Game Progress**: Your current level, highest score, coins earned, and owned in-game items (skins, themes).
- **Device Information**: Device model, operating system version, screen resolution, and language/region settings — used for analytics and to optimize gameplay.
- **Session Data**: Number of app sessions, session duration, and timezone — used for analytics.
- **App Version**: The version of Frenzy Stack you are running.
- **Usage Analytics**: In-game events such as levels started/completed, game overs, purchases, and feature usage — logged via Firebase Analytics.

### 1.3 Advertising Identifiers
If you have not purchased "Remove Ads":
- **Google Advertising ID (Android)** / **Apple IDFA (iOS)**: Used by Google AdMob to serve personalized or contextual ads. On iOS 14+, you will be asked for App Tracking Transparency (ATT) permission before the advertising identifier is accessed.

---

## 2. How We Use Your Information

We use the collected information for the following purposes:

| Purpose | Data Used |
|---|---|
| Display global leaderboard | Player ID, Player Name, Score |
| Sync game progress across reinstalls | Player ID, Level, Coins, Owned items |
| Serve advertisements | Advertising ID (if ads not removed) |
| Analyze gameplay to improve the game | Anonymous analytics events |
| Provide in-app purchases | Handled entirely by App Store / Play Store |
| Crash reporting and debugging | Device info, App version |

**We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to any third party.**

---

## 3. Third-Party Services

Frenzy Stack uses the following third-party services. Each service has its own privacy policy:

### Google AdMob
- **Purpose**: Display banner ads, rewarded video ads, and interstitial ads.
- **Data Collected**: Advertising identifiers, IP address, device information.
- **Privacy Policy**: https://policies.google.com/privacy
- **Opt-Out**: Purchase "Remove Ads" within the app, or reset your Advertising ID in device settings.

### Firebase Analytics (Google)
- **Purpose**: Understand how players interact with the game; improve features.
- **Data Collected**: Anonymous usage events, device information, app version.
- **Privacy Policy**: https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy
- **Data Retention**: 60 days (default Firebase Analytics retention).

### Supabase
- **Purpose**: Store global leaderboard data and optionally sync player progress.
- **Data Stored**: Anonymous Player ID, Player Name, Score, Level, Owned items.
- **Privacy Policy**: https://supabase.com/privacy
- **Data Location**: EU (Frankfurt, Germany) data center.

### Google Play Billing / Apple In-App Purchase
- **Purpose**: Process in-app purchases (Remove Ads, Coin Packs, VIP Bundle).
- **Data Handled**: Entirely by Google / Apple. We do not receive or store your payment information.
- **Google Privacy Policy**: https://policies.google.com/privacy
- **Apple Privacy Policy**: https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy

